rica, the surname <i>Miller</i> has absorbed many cognate surnames from other languages, for example German <b>Müller</b> (see   Mueller  ), Dutch   Mulder   and   Molenaar  , French   Meunier  , Italian   Molinaro  , Spanish   Molinero  , Hungarian <b>Molnár</b> (see   Molnar  ), Slovenian, Croatian, and Serbian   Mlinar  , Polish <b>Młynarz</b> or <b>Młynarczyk</b> (see   Mlynarczyk  ). <i>Miller</i> (including in the senses below) is the seventh most frequent surname in the US.","South German, Swiss German, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of <b>Müller</b> ‘miller’ (see   Mueller  ) and, in North America, also an altered form of this. This form of the surname is also found in other European countries, notably in Poland, Denmark, France (mainly Alsace and Lorraine), and Czechia; compare 3 below.","Americanized form of Polish, Czech, Croatian, Serbian, and Slovenian   Miler   ‘miller’, a surname of German origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Millar","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Miller  . It is also found in Ireland (especially Antrim)."]},{"name":"Mueller","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Otto, Hans, Erwin, Fritz, Gerhard, Klaus, Heinz, Helmut, Wolfgang, Manfred, Horst.","German (mainly <b>Müller</b>) and Jewish (Ashkenazic; also <b>Müller</b>); Dutch: occupational name for a miller, Middle High German <i>müller</i>, German <i>Müller</i>. In Germany, <i>Müller</i>, <i>Mueller</i> is the most frequent of all surnames; in the US it is often changed to   Miller   or appears as   Muller  . See also   Mulder  ."]},{"name":"Milner","meanings":["English (northern, especially Yorkshire): variant of   Miller  , retaining the <i>-n-</i> of the Middle English word <i>milnere</i> ‘miller’.","German: variant of <b>Müller</b> (see   Mueller  )."]},{"name":"Millward","meanings":["English (mainly West Midlands): occupational name from Middle English <i>milne-ward</i>, <i>mille-ward</i> ‘keeper of a mill, miller’ (Old English <i>mylen-weard</i>). In southern England and the West Midlands this was a standard medieval term for a miller. Compare   Miller  ."]},{"name":"McMiller","meanings":["Scottish: patronymic from the occupational byname   Miller  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Miller was born in 1490, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Mrs John Miller. He died in 1575, in his hometown, at the age of 85."},"et":{"1490–1575":"1490–1575","1515–Male":"1515–Surnud","about 1515":"umbes 1515","1575":"1575","1490":"1490","1515":"1515","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of Carne, , Dorset, England":"Cerne, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1490–1575":"1490–1575","1515–Male":"1515–Kuollut","about 1515":"noin 1515","1575":"1575","1490":"1490","1515":"1515","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of Carne, , Dorset, England":"Cerne, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1490–1575":"1490–1575","1515–Male":"1515–Décédé","about 1515":"environ 1515","1575":"1575","1490":"1490","1515":"1515","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Of Carne, , Dorset, England":"Cerne, Dorset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John Miller est né en 1490, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs John Miller. Il est décédé en 1575, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 85 ans."},"de":{"1490–1575":"1490–1575","1515–Male":"1515–Verstorben","about 1515":"um 1515","1575":"1575","1490":"1490","1515":"1515","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","Of Carne, , Dorset, England":"Cerne, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"John Miller wurde 1490 in England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mit Mrs John Miller mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1575 im Alter von 85 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1490–1575":"1490–1575","1515–Male":"1515–Desede","about 1515":"about 1515","1575":"1575","1490":"14